  {
    "time": 1774000000000,
    "blocks": [
      {
        "id": "title1",
        "type": "title",
        "data": {
          "text": "The Future of Note-Taking",
          "alignText": "text-left",
          "titleType": "H1"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "header1",
        "type": "header",
        "data": {
          "text": "Introduction",
          "level": 2
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "p1",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {
          "text": "Note-taking has evolved dramatically over the past decade. From handwritten journals to fully digital ecosystems, the way we capture and process information has changed in both form and function. Modern tools allow users to organize thoughts, collaborate in real time, and integrate multimedia seamlessly into their workflows."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "p2",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {
          "text": "Applications like Editor.js provide a block-based approach that mirrors how people naturally think—breaking information into chunks. This makes editing, rearranging, and rendering content far more intuitive compared to traditional text editors."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "header2",
        "type": "header",
        "data": {
          "text": "Key Benefits",
          "level": 2
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "list1",
        "type": "list",
        "data": {
          "style": "unordered",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": "Modular content structure for flexibility",
              "meta": {},
              "items": []
            },
            {
              "content": "Easy integration with modern frameworks like React",
              "meta": {},
              "items": []
            },
            {
              "content": "Custom block rendering for full design control",
              "meta": {},
              "items": []
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "header3",
        "type": "header",
        "data": {
          "text": "Steps to Build a Note App",
          "level": 3
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "list2",
        "type": "list",
        "data": {
          "style": "ordered",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": "Set up your frontend with React or Next.js",
              "meta": {},
              "items": []
            },
            {
              "content": "Integrate Editor.js and configure tools",
              "meta": {},
              "items": []
            },
            {
              "content": "Store structured JSON data in your backend",
              "meta": {},
              "items": []
            },
            {
              "content": "Render content using a custom renderer or Editor.js viewer",
              "meta": {},
              "items": []
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "header4",
        "type": "header",
        "data": {
          "text": "Checklist Example",
          "level": 3
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "list3",
        "type": "list",
        "data": {
          "style": "checklist",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": "Design UI layout",
              "meta": {
                "checked": true
              },
              "items": []
            },
            {
              "content": "Implement Editor.js renderer",
              "meta": {
                "checked": false
              },
              "items": []
            },
            {
              "content": "Optimize performance for large datasets",
              "meta": {
                "checked": false
              },
              "items": []
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "header5",
        "type": "header",
        "data": {
          "text": "Conclusion",
          "level": 2
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "p3",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {
          "text": "Building a modern note-taking application requires balancing performance, usability, and flexibility. By leveraging tools like Editor.js and combining them with custom renderers, developers can create powerful and scalable systems that adapt to a wide range of use cases. Whether for personal journaling or collaborative workflows, structured content is the future."
        }
      }
    ],
    "version": "2.31.5"
  },
