          "type": "header",
          "data": {
            "text": "<b><i>Advanced Considerations</i></b>",
            "level": 2
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "2I5_rZhIJL",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "data": {
            "text": "As your note-taking app grows, you may encounter challenges such as:"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "RlKd3nWVXl",
          "type": "list",
          "data": {
            "style": "unordered",
            "meta": {},
            "items": [
              {
                "content": "Handling extremely large documents efficiently\n",
                "meta": {},
                "items": []
              },
              {
                "content": "Supporting nested lists, tables, and embedded media\n",
                "meta": {},
                "items": []
              },
              {
                "content": "Ensuring smooth collaboration between multiple users\n",
                "meta": {},
                "items": []
              },
              {
                "content": "Maintaining accessibility and responsive design\n",
                "meta": {},
                "items": []
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "3MbL3qWVjG",
          "type": "header",
          "data": {
            "text": "<b><i>Conclusion</i></b>",
            "level": 2
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "GEwtL25qeJ",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "data": {
            "text": "Building a modern note-taking application requires balancing performance, usability, and flexibility. By leveraging tools like Editor.js and combining them with custom renderers, developers can create powerful and scalable systems that adapt to a wide range of use cases. Whether for personal journaling or collaborative workflows, structured content is the future."
          }
        }
      ],
      "version": "2.31.5"
    }
  },
